name: toot status message
func:
msg.payload = "#Automated Flight Status:\r\n"    
    + flow.get("LaunchDet") + "\r\n"
    + flow.get("ApogeeDet") + "\r\n"
    + flow.get("SeperationDet") + "\r\n"
    + "Altitude: " + flow.get("altitude") + "\r\n"
    + "Max Altitude: " + flow.get("MaxAltitude") + "\r\n"
    + "Max G Force: " + flow.get("MaxG") + "\r\n"
;
return msg;

info:
in your settings.js file
(if linux, default is ~/.nodered/settings.js)

add the below line before
module.exports, replacing 'yourpassword' with
the sudo password for the 'user' account of your
single board computer. this will allow you to use
this variable in any of the commands that may
need super user access, without hard coding passwords
in your flow.


process.env.RTPW = 'yourpassword';
